# Post-deploy live verify (mandatory)

After **any** production deploy, verify live surfaces match disk **before** telling the founder it shipped.

## Triggers

- `./scripts/deploy-www-cloudflare.sh` (canonical www)
- `./scripts/deploy-www-vercel.sh` (legacy — remove after CF cutover)
- `./scripts/deploy-platform-railway.sh` or `railway up` on `platform-api`
- Any manual Vercel/Railway production deploy

## Required flow

```bash
EXPECTED_SHA=$(git rev-parse HEAD)

# deploy command here — if it fails, alert immediately:
python3 scripts/nf_post_deploy_verify.py --deploy-failed "www vercel" --surface www || true

# after successful deploy:
python3 scripts/nf_post_deploy_verify.py --expected-sha "$EXPECTED_SHA"
```

Use `--surface www`, `platform`, or `both` (default) when only one surface changed.

## What “new version” means

| Surface | Live proof |
|---------|------------|
| Platform | `/api/public/chat/health` → `git_sha` matches `EXPECTED_SHA` |
| WWW | `verify_chat_greeting_coupling.py --live` PASS |
| Intake E2E | `nf_intake_e2e.py` — submit + poll `email_archive_status=delivered` (skipped when webhook tracking off) |

## Telegram alert

On deploy failure **or** verify failure, `nf_post_deploy_verify.py` messages founder via Telegram.

Requires in `~/.sina/secrets.env` (never commit):

- `TELEGRAM_NOETFIELD_OPS_BOT_TOKEN`
- `TELEGRAM_OPS_CHAT_ID` — founder’s numeric chat id

Missing chat id → verify still runs; failure prints to stderr.

## Forbidden

- Reporting deploy PASS without live verify
- Skipping Telegram alert when deploy or verify fails
- Treating “build succeeded” as “live is current”
